{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018H4SGR6cdK1dzJcYiwu9aQ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me compile the complete report:\n\n## Report\n\n### 1. Full Content of multi-agent-orchestration-contract.md\n\nThe file `/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/docs/multi-agent-orchestration-contract.md` defines a first-class Rust contract for orchestrating multiple agents with the following structure:\n\n**Key sections:**\n- **Objective**: Spawn workers in parallel for independent tasks, receive structured task notifications, and synthesize results into a coordinator-level summary\n- **Core Rust Types** (§4):\n  - `OrchestrationMode` enum (Disabled, Coordinator)\n  - `TaskCriticality` enum (Blocking, Sidecar)\n  - `WorkerTaskSpec` struct with task_id, title, prompt, criticality, owner_scope\n  - `WorkerResultNotification` with task_id, status, summary, artifacts\n  - `WorkerStatus` enum (Running, Completed, Failed, Cancelled)\n  - `MultiAgentOrchestrator` async trait with methods: `spawn_parallel()`, `handle_notification()`, `synthesize_summary()`, `stop_task()`\n  - `CoordinatorSummary` struct with completed count, failed count, key_findings, next_actions\n\n- **Policy Requirements** (§5): Independent tasks launched in parallel, blocking critical-path work constraints, synthesized summaries required, self-contained prompts with ownership boundaries, idempotent task stops\n\n- **Error Taxonomy** (§6): OrchestrationError enum with variants like DisabledByMode, InvalidTaskSpec, PolicyViolation, NotificationMalformed, TaskNotFound, SpawnFailed, SynthesisFailed\n\n- **Acceptance Matrix** (§8):\n  - Contract tests: policy validation, notification parsing, synthesis requirements\n  - Integration tests: 3 parallel tasks, mixed result statuses, idempotent stop_task\n  - CLI behavior tests: tool controls, mode blocking, user-visible summary\n\n---\n\n### 2. Acceptance Test Patterns (Examples)\n\n**Pattern 1: Contract Tests** (from `kairos_acceptance_tests.rs` lines 75-104)\n```rust\n/// AC: mode resolution is deterministic for same inputs.\n#[test]\nfn contract_mode_resolution_is_deterministic_for_same_inputs() {\n    let service = svc();\n    let ctx = resolve_ctx(\n        AssistantMode::Kairos,\n        Some(AssistantMode::KairosBrief),\n        default_policy(),\n    );\n\n    let a = service.resolve_mode(ctx.clone());\n    let b = service.resolve_mode(ctx);\n\n    assert_eq!(a.effective_mode, b.effective_mode, \"effective_mode must be deterministic\");\n    assert_eq!(a.source, b.source, \"source must be deterministic\");\n    assert_eq!(a.visible_tools, b.visible_tools, \"visible_tools must be deterministic\");\n    assert!(a.error.is_none());\n    assert!(b.error.is_none());\n}\n```\n\n**Pattern 2: Integration Tests with Async/Mocks** (from `bridge_mode_acceptance_tests.rs` lines 243-267)\n```rust\n/// AC: create → fetch → archive happy path passes.\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn integration_create_fetch_archive_happy_path() {\n    let session_id = \"session_happy\";\n    let client = MockCcrClient::for_happy_path(session_id, RemoteSessionState::Running);\n    let svc = ApplicationRemoteSessionService::new(client, true);\n\n    // Step 1: create\n    let created = svc.create_session(sample_create_request()).await.expect(\"create must succeed\");\n    assert_eq!(created.session_id, session_id);\n    assert_eq!(created.state, RemoteSessionState::Running);\n\n    // Step 2: fetch\n    let fetched = svc.fetch_session(session_id).await.expect(\"fetch must succeed\");\n    assert_eq!(fetched.session_id, session_id);\n\n    // Step 3: archive\n    svc.archive_session(session_id, short_timeout()).await.expect(\"archive must succeed\");\n}\n```\n\n**Pattern 3: Serialization/Contract Tests** (from `provider/tests/contract.rs` lines 21-55)\nTests round-trip serialization, bijective mappings, and data-transformation assertions without HTTP calls.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Crate Structure and Test Location\n\n**Directory Structure:**\n```\ncrates/\n├── application/          (services, domain logic)\n├── bootstrap/            (initialization)\n├── cli/                  (CLI interface)\n├── config/               (configuration)\n├── cron/                 (scheduling)\n├── domain/               (core domain models)\n├── mcp-runtime/          (MCP protocol runtime)\n├── platform/             (platform abstractions)\n├── ports/                (adapter interfaces)\n├── provider/             (provider implementations)\n├── remote-runtime/       (remote execution)\n├── session/              (session management)\n├── state-store/          (persistence)\n└── tools/                (tool implementations)\n```\n\n**Test Organization Pattern:**\n\n1. **Unit/Contract Tests**: Embedded in `src/` as `#[cfg(test)] mod` blocks\n   - Location: `crates/application/src/lib.rs` declares:\n     - `#[cfg(test)] mod bridge_mode_acceptance_tests;`\n     - `#[cfg(test)] mod coordinator_mode_acceptance_tests;`\n     - `#[cfg(test)] mod kairos_acceptance_tests;`\n     - `#[cfg(test)] mod multi_agent_orchestrator_tests;`\n     - `#[cfg(test)] mod remote_session_service_tests;`\n\n2. **Integration Tests**: Separate `tests/` directories\n   - Location: `crates/provider/tests/contract.rs`\n   - Location: `crates/ports/tests/llm_client_contract.rs`\n   - Location: `crates/bootstrap/tests/`\n   - Location: `crates/domain/tests/`\n\n3. **Internal Contract Tests**: As `*_tests.rs` modules in `src/`\n   - `crates/mcp-runtime/src/chicago_mcp_acceptance_tests.rs`\n   - `crates/remote-runtime/src/contracts_tests.rs`\n\n**Test File Naming Conventions:**\n- Acceptance tests: `*_acceptance_tests.rs`\n- Contract tests: `contract.rs` or `contracts_tests.rs`\n- Organized by feature/module being tested\n\n**Test Structure Pattern:**\n- Section comments (§7.1, §7.2, §7.3) mark test categories from spec contracts\n- Helper functions at top for test setup/fixtures\n- Test functions follow AC 