{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01X92FCrcbR8kwMnU2zr3fhd","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Multi-Agent Orchestration Contract Spec (Rust)\n2\t\n3\t## 1. Objective\n4\t\n5\tDefine a first-class Rust contract for orchestrating multiple agents that can:\n6\t\n7\t1. Spawn workers in parallel for independent tasks.\n8\t2. Receive worker results as structured task notifications.\n9\t3. Synthesize results into a single coordinator-level summary.\n10\t\n11\tThis is required capability, not optional behavior.\n12\t\n13\t## 2. Evidence from Current Code\n14\t\n15\t1. `tools.ts:3` imports `AgentTool`.\n16\t2. `tools.ts:12` imports `TaskStopTool`.\n17\t3. `tools.ts:288-295` coordinator mode allows `AgentTool` + `TaskStopTool`.\n18\t4. `coordinator/coordinatorMode.ts:140` coordinator must report launched agents and wait for results.\n19\t5. `coordinator/coordinatorMode.ts:144` worker results arrive as `<task-notification>`.\n20\t6. `coordinator/coordinatorMode.ts:213` explicit parallel-launch guidance.\n21\t7. `cli/print.ts:1939-2015` `task-notification` mode handling in main loop.\n22\t8. `main.tsx:3035` `teamContext` initialization supports teammate spawning.\n23\t9. `main.tsx:3857` hidden `--teammate-mode` supports `auto|tmux|in-process`.\n24\t\n25\t## 3. Rust Boundary Mapping\n26\t\n27\t1. `crates/api-types`\n28\tTask notification schema, worker task IDs, orchestration state enums.\n29\t\n30\t2. `crates/app-services`\n31\tOrchestration policy: fan-out eligibility, blocking vs sidecar tasks, synthesis requirements.\n32\t\n33\t3. `crates/tool-runtime`\n34\tTool surface integration (`AgentTool`, `TaskStopTool`, message routing hooks).\n35\t\n36\t4. `crates/remote-runtime`\n37\tOptional remote worker lifecycle (for remote agents/tasks).\n38\t\n39\t5. `crates/state-store`\n40\tTask metadata/transcript pointers and orchestration checkpoints.\n41\t\n42\t6. `crates/config`\n43\tMode and limits (`max_parallel_agents`, teammate mode defaults, guardrails).\n44\t\n45\t7. `bins/app-cli` / `crates/ui-tui`\n46\tDisplay status only; no scheduling policy decisions.\n47\t\n48\t## 4. Core Contracts (Rust Sketch)\n49\t\n50\t```rust\n51\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]\n52\tpub enum OrchestrationMode {\n53\t    Disabled,\n54\t    Coordinator,\n55\t}\n56\t\n57\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]\n58\tpub enum TaskCriticality {\n59\t    Blocking,\n60\t    Sidecar,\n61\t}\n62\t\n63\t#[derive(Debug, Clone)]\n64\tpub struct WorkerTaskSpec {\n65\t    pub task_id: String,\n66\t    pub title: String,\n67\t    pub prompt: String,\n68\t    pub criticality: TaskCriticality,\n69\t    pub owner_scope: String, // e.g. file/module boundary\n70\t}\n71\t\n72\t#[derive(Debug, Clone)]\n73\tpub struct WorkerResultNotification {\n74\t    pub task_id: String,\n75\t    pub status: WorkerStatus,\n76\t    pub summary: String,\n77\t    pub artifacts: Vec<String>,\n78\t}\n79\t\n80\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]\n81\tpub enum WorkerStatus {\n82\t    Running,\n83\t    Completed,\n84\t    Failed,\n85\t    Cancelled,\n86\t}\n87\t\n88\t#[async_trait::async_trait]\n89\tpub trait MultiAgentOrchestrator: Send + Sync {\n90\t    async fn spawn_parallel(\n91\t        &self,\n92\t        tasks: Vec<WorkerTaskSpec>,\n93\t    ) -> Result<Vec<String>, OrchestrationError>; // returns worker ids\n94\t\n95\t    async fn handle_notification(\n96\t        &self,\n97\t        notification: WorkerResultNotification,\n98\t    ) -> Result<(), OrchestrationError>;\n99\t\n100\t    async fn synthesize_summary(\n101\t        &self,\n102\t        task_ids: &[String],\n103\t    ) -> Result<CoordinatorSummary, OrchestrationError>;\n104\t\n105\t    async fn stop_task(&self, task_id: &str) -> Result<(), OrchestrationError>;\n106\t}\n107\t\n108\t#[derive(Debug, Clone)]\n109\tpub struct CoordinatorSummary {\n110\t    pub completed: usize,\n111\t    pub failed: usize,\n112\t    pub key_findings: Vec<String>,\n113\t    pub next_actions: Vec<String>,\n114\t}\n115\t```\n116\t\n117\t## 5. Policy Requirements\n118\t\n119\t1. Independent tasks must be launched in parallel when no shared write scope exists.\n120\t2. Blocking critical-path work should not be delegated if local progress depends on it immediately.\n121\t3. Coordinator must produce synthesized summary from notifications; no raw pass-through only.\n122\t4. Worker prompts must be self-contained and include ownership boundaries.\n123\t5. Task stop requests must be idempotent and produce deterministic task terminal status.\n124\t\n125\t## 6. Error Taxonomy\n126\t\n127\t```rust\n128\tpub enum OrchestrationError {\n129\t    DisabledByMode,\n130\t    InvalidTaskSpec,\n131\t    PolicyViolation,     // e.g. conflicting write scopes in parallel group\n132\t    NotificationMalformed,\n133\t    TaskNotFound,\n134\t    SpawnFailed(String),\n135\t    SynthesisFailed(String),\n136\t}\n137\t```\n138\t\n139\t## 7. Constants Classification\n140\t\n141\t1. `api-types`: orchestration state names, notification type keys.\n142\t2. `config`: max parallel count, timeout defaults, teammate mode defaults.\n143\t3. `core-domain`: invariants (e.g. terminal-state transition rules).\n144\t4. `tool-runtime`: tool-name constants and internal routing keys.\n145\t5. `ui-tui`: display labels for task status and coordinator summaries.\n146\t\n147\t## 8. Acceptance Matrix\n148\t\n149\t### 8.1 Contract tests\n150\t\n151\t1. Parallel fan-out rejects overlapping write scopes when policy forbids them.\n152\t2. Notification parsing enforces structured payload fields (`task_id`, `status`, `summary`).\n153\t3. Synthesis requires completed/failed accounting and deterministic summary structure.\n154\t\n155\t### 8.2 Integration tests\n156\t\n157\t1. Spawn 3 independent tasks in parallel and receive 3 notifications.\n158\t2. Mixed result statuses (completed/failed/cancelled) are aggregated correctly.\n159\t3. `stop_task` on already-terminal task is idempotent and non-fatal.\n160\t\n161\t### 8.3 CLI behavior tests\n162\t\n163\t1. Coordinator mode exposes multi-agent controls and task status updates.\n164\t2. Non-coordinator mode blocks orchestration calls with explicit policy error.\n165\t3. Final user-visible summary includes launched tasks, findings, and next actions.\n166\t\n167\t## 9. Relationship to Existing Contracts\n168\t\n169\t1. Extends `coordinator-mode-contract.md` with execution semantics.\n170\t2. Depends on `integration-contracts.md` shared error envelope and correlation IDs.\n171\t3. Must be listed in `spec-lock-v1.md` before implementation phase begins.\n172\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6429a853-3cab-4876-b6cc-9209ef0cfb79","uuid":"ab3a690b-e337-4af8-8b1e-b5757694594e","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:36:16.759Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/yaxin/Projects/rust_projects/ccode/docs/multi-agent-orchestration-contract.md","content":"# Multi-Agent Orchestration Contract Spec (Rust)\n\n## 1. Objective\n\nDefine a first-class Rust contract for orchestrating multiple agents that can:\n\n1. Spawn workers in parallel for independent tasks.\n2. Receive worker results as structured task notifications.\n3. Synthesize results into a single coordinator-level summary.\n\nThis is required capability, not optional behavior.\n\n## 2. Evidence from Current Code\n\n1. `tools.ts:3` imports `AgentTool`.\n2. `tools.ts:12` imports `TaskStopTool`.\n3. `tools.ts:288-295` coordinator mode allows `AgentTool` + `TaskStopTool`.\n4. `coordinator/coordinatorMode.ts:140` coordinator must report launched agents and wait for results.\n5. `coordinator/coordinatorMode.ts:144` worker results arrive as `<task-notification>`.\n6. `coordinator/coordinatorMode.ts:213` explicit parallel-launch guidance.\n7. `cli/print.ts:1939-2015` `task-notification` mode handling in main loop.\n8. `main.tsx:3035` `teamContext` initialization supports teammate spawning.\n9. `main.tsx:3857` hidden `--teammate-mode` supports `auto|tmux|in-process`.\n\n## 3. Rust Boundary Mapping\n\n1. `crates/api-types`\nTask notification schema, worker task IDs, orchestration state enums.\n\n2. `crates/app-services`\nOrchestration policy: fan-out eligibility, blocking vs sidecar tasks, synthesis requirements.\n\n3. `crates/tool-runtime`\nTool surface integration (`AgentTool`, `TaskStopTool`, message routing hooks).\n\n4. `crates/remote-runtime`\nOptional remote worker lifecycle (for remote agents/tasks).\n\n5. `crates/state-store`\nTask metadata/transcript pointers and orchestration checkpoints.\n\n6. `crates/config`\nMode and limits (`max_parallel_agents`, teammate mode defaults, guardrails).\n\n7. `bins/app-cli` / `crates/ui-tui`\nDisplay status only; no scheduling policy decisions.\n\n## 4. Core Contracts (Rust Sketch)\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]\npub enum OrchestrationMode {\n    Disabled,\n    Coordinator,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]\npub enum TaskCriticality {\n    Blocking,\n    Sidecar,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone)]\npub struct WorkerTaskSpec {\n    pub task_id: String,\n    pub title: String,\n    pub prompt: String,\n    pub criticality: TaskCriticality,\n    pub owner_scope: String, // e.g. file/module boundary\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone)]\npub struct WorkerResultNotification {\n    pub task_id: String,\n    pub status: WorkerStatus,\n    pub summary: String,\n    pub artifacts: Vec<String>,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]\npub enum WorkerStatus {\n    Running,\n    Completed,\n    Failed,\n    Cancelled,\n}\n\n#[async_trait::async_trait]\npub trait MultiAgentOrchestrator: Send + Sync {\n    async fn spawn_parallel(\n        &self,\n        tasks: Vec<WorkerTaskSpec>,\n    ) -> Result<Vec<String>, OrchestrationError>; // returns worker ids\n\n    async fn handle_notification(\n        &self,\n        notification: WorkerResultNotification,\n    ) -> Result<(), OrchestrationError>;\n\n    async fn synthesize_summary(\n        &self,\n        task_ids: &[String],\n    ) -> Result<CoordinatorSummary, OrchestrationError>;\n\n    async fn stop_task(&self, task_id: &str) -> Result<(), OrchestrationError>;\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone)]\npub struct CoordinatorSummary {\n    pub completed: usize,\n    pub failed: usize,\n    pub key_findings: Vec<String>,\n    pub next_actions: Vec<String>,\n}\n```\n\n## 5. Policy Requirements\n\n1. Independent tasks must be launched in parallel when no shared write scope exists.\n2. Blocking critical-path work should not be delegated if local progress depends on it immediately.\n3. Coordinator must produce synthesized summary from notifications; no raw pass-through only.\n4. Worker prompts must be self-contained and include ownership boundaries.\n5. Task stop requests must be idempotent and produce deterministic task terminal status.\n\n## 6. Error Taxonomy\n\n```rust\npub enum OrchestrationError {\n    DisabledByMode,\n    InvalidTaskSpec,\n    PolicyViolation,     // e.g. conflicting write scopes in parallel group\n    NotificationMalformed,\n    TaskNotFound,\n    SpawnFailed(String),\n    SynthesisFailed(String),\n}\n```\n\n## 7. Constants Classification\n\n1. `api-types`: orchestration state names, notification type keys.\n2. `config`: max parallel count, timeout defaults, teammate mode defaults.\n3. `core-domain`: invariants (e.g. terminal-state transition rules).\n4. `tool-runtime`: tool-name constants and internal routing keys.\n5. `ui-tui`: display labels for task status and coordinator summaries.\n\n## 8. Acceptance Matrix\n\n### 8.1 Contract tests\n\n1. Parallel fan-out rejects overlapping write scopes when policy forbids them.\n2. Notification parsing enforces structured payload fields (`task_id`, `status`, `summary`).\n3. Synthesis requires completed/failed accounting and deterministic summary structure.\n\n### 8.2 Integration tests\n\n1. Spawn 3 independent tasks in parallel and receive 3 notifications.\n2. Mixed result statuses (completed/failed/cancelled) are aggregated correctly.\n3. `stop_task` on already-terminal task is idempotent and non-fatal.\n\n### 8.3 CLI behavior tests\n\n1. Coordinator mode exposes multi-agent controls and task status updates.\n2. Non-coordinator mode blocks orchestration calls with explicit policy error.\n3. Final user-visible summary includes launched tasks, findings, and next actions.\n\n## 9. Relationship to Existing Contracts\n\n1. Extends `coordinator-mode-contract.md` with execution semantics.\n2. Depends on `integration-contracts.md` shared error envelope and correlation IDs.\n3. Must be listed in `spec-lock-v1.md` before implementation phase begins.\n","numLines":172,"startLine":1,"totalLines":172}}}
